DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Serum Immunologic IgG Result Upper Limit of Normal Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: a numeric value, units of measure not specified, for the upper limit of normal amount for IgG, an immunoglobulin isotype (subclass) that characterizes secondary immune responses, serum immunologic lab.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Serum Immunologic IgG Result
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for IgG, an immunoglobulin isotype (subclass) that characterizes secondary immune responses.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: Serum Immunologic; refers to immunologic features of or immunologic tests done on serum.:An immunoglobulin isotype (subclass) that characterizes secondary immune responses.  This isotype is further broken down into several smaller subclasses (IgG1, IgG2a, IgG2b, IgG3 in the mouse; IgG1-4 in the human), and each subclass is differentially synthesized and secreted into the serum upon differential immune stimuli.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: Pertaining to serologic tests to determine the presence of immunologic factors or evidence of an immune response.

An immunoglobulin isotype (subclass) that characterizes secondary immune responses.  This isotype is further broken down into several smaller subclasses (IgG1, IgG2a, IgG2b, IgG3 in the mouse; IgG1-4 in the human), and each subclass is differentially synthesized and secreted into the serum upon differential immune stimuli.

ValueDomain.preferredName: Serum Immunologic IgG Lab Upper Limit of Normal Value
ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: a numeric value, units of measure not specified, for the upper limit of normal amount of immunoglobulin type G (IgG) found in blood serum.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: The top value of the range of statistical characteristics that are supposed to represent accepted standard, non-pathological pattern for particular laboratory result or other quantitative parameter.:A numerical quantity measured or assigned or computed.

Concepts.definition: The top value of the range of statistical characteristics that are supposed to represent accepted standard, non-pathological pattern for particular laboratory result or other quantitative parameter.
A numerical quantity measured or assigned or computed.
